    Title: Theatetus
    Locus: 176 B
By: Plato
Tags:
  - 944
  - 900
---
We ought to fly away from earth to heaven as quickly as we can; and to fly
away is to become like God, as far as this is possible; and to become like
him, is to become holy, just, and wise.
